modules.description: Provides functions to parse and evaluate Dream .eml templates embedded in OCaml code, converting them into strings. Works with raw string literals and template syntax containing OCaml expressions. Enables inline templating in web applications, allowing dynamic content generation within HTML-like structures.

Processes a Dream Embedded ML string, transforming it into OCaml code by expanding embedded expressions and handling syntax extensions. Works with strings and OCaml AST expressions, leveraging a custom ppx extension for inlining. Used to generate dynamic OCaml code at compile time from embedded templates.
